title: Packet Diagram
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A packet diagram renders binary frame layouts at the bit level — the kind of diagram you see in RFC documents for TCP, UDP, IP, and other protocol specifications. Use it when documenting network protocols, hardware registers, or any fixed-width binary format. ''New in Mermaid 11.'' Uses `packet-beta`.

---

!! Basic example

```
packet-beta
    0-7: "Version"
    8-15: "IHL"
    16-31: "Total Length"
    32-63: "Source IP"
    64-95: "Destination IP"
    96+: "Data"
```

$$$text/vnd.tiddlywiki.mermaid
