$$$

---

!! Real-world example: TCP segment

```
packet-beta
    title TCP Segment
    0-15: "Source Port"
    16-31: "Destination Port"
    32-63: "Sequence Number"
    64-95: "Acknowledgment Number"
    96-99: "Data Offset"
    100-105: "Reserved"
    106: "URG"
    107: "ACK"
    108: "PSH"
    109: "RST"
    110: "SYN"
    111: "FIN"
    112-127: "Window Size"
    128-143: "Checksum"
    144-159: "Urgent Pointer"
    160-191: "Options"
    192+: "Data (variable)"
```

$$$text/vnd.tiddlywiki.mermaid
