---

!! Syntax

```
packet-beta
    title Optional title
    0-7: "Field name"
    8-15: "Another field"
    16+: "Variable-length field"
```

* Each line defines a bit field: `start-end: "Label"` or `start+: "Label"` for open-ended fields.
* Bit numbering starts at 0.
* Fields are rendered left-to-right, wrapping to the next row when the line width is exceeded.
* The default line width is 32 bits (matches most protocol diagrams).

!! Tips

* Single-bit fields (like TCP flags) use a single number: `106: "SYN"`.
* `+` suffix means "remaining bits" — use it only for the last field.
* `title` is optional but helps when embedding multiple packet diagrams on one page.
* This diagram type has a niche audience but is very effective for technical documentation.

